  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "On Jordan&#39;s bank the Baptist&#39;s cry Announces that the Lord is nigh; Come, then, and hearken, for he brings Glad tidings from the King of kings!",
    "v2": "Then cleansed be every breast from sin; Make straight the way for God within; Prepare we in our hearts a home, Where such a mighty Guest may come.",
    "v3": "For Thou art our Salvation, Lord, Our Refuge, and our great Reward. Without Thy grace our souls must fade And wither like a flow&#39;r decayed.",
    "v4": "Stretch forth Thine hand, to heal our sore, And make us rise and fall no more; Once more upon Thy people shine, And fill the world with love divine.",
    "v5": "To Him Who left the throne of Heav&#39;n To save mankind, all praise be giv&#39;n; Like praise be to the Father done, And Holy Spirit, Three in One."
  },
